The paper discusses the use of deep learning models for remote sensing image recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the security issues related to these models, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category. The use of adversarial examples to attack these models involves the manipulation of input data, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of these attacks on remote sensing applications, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
